task.implementation:
In deployment/docker-compose.flows.yml, change:
  OPTUNA_STORAGE_URL: ${OPTUNA_STORAGE_URL:-postgresql+psycopg2://minivess:minivess_secret@postgres:5432/optuna}
To:
  OPTUNA_STORAGE_URL: ${OPTUNA_STORAGE_URL:-postgresql+psycopg2://${POSTGRES_USER:-minivess}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:-minivess_secret}@${POSTGRES_DOCKER_HOST:-postgres}:5432/${POSTGRES_DB_OPTUNA:-optuna}}
Note: The outer fallback still works since OPTUNA_STORAGE_URL in .env takes priority.

Expand Makefile scan and add sbom target:

sbom:
  @echo "Generating SBOM for MinIVess base image..."
  @which trivy || (echo "Install trivy first: make install-trivy" && exit 1)
  @mkdir -p sbom/
  @trivy image --format cyclonedx --output sbom/minivess-base-sbom.json \
    minivess-base:latest
  @echo "SBOM written to sbom/minivess-base-sbom.json"

install-trivy:
  @curl -sfL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aquasecurity/trivy/main/contrib/install.sh \
    | sh -s -- -b /usr/local/bin
  @echo "Trivy installed at /usr/local/bin/trivy"

Add sbom/ to .gitignore (SBOMs are artifacts, not source).
Add sbom/ to .dockerignore (not needed in images).
